{% extends 'polygon/polygon_base.jinja2' %}

{% block title %}Register - {% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <h1 class="ui header">Enable Polygon</h1>
  <p>You will use EOJ username and password to login to Polygon.</p>
  <p>Here are the terms of use.</p>
  <div class="ui message">
  <ul class="list">
    <li class="item">You can use Polygon to develop problems only.</li>
    <li class="item">You should not submit files containing malicious code:
      <ul class="list">
        <li class="item">trojan horses;</li>
        <li class="item">rootkits;</li>
        <li class="item">backdoors;</li>
        <li class="item">viruses.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li class="item">Your code is not allowed to:
    <ul class="list">
      <li class="item">access the network;</li>
      <li class="item">work with any files except those explicitly specified in the problem statement;</li>
      <li class="item">attack system security;</li>
      <li class="item">execute other programs and create new processes;</li>
      <li class="item">change file system permissions;</li>
      <li class="item">work with subdirectories;</li>
      <li class="item">create or manipulate any GUI items (windows, dialog boxes, etc);</li>
      <li class="item">work with external devices (sound, printer, etc);</li>
      <li class="item">work with OS registry;</li>
      <li class="item">do anything else that can stir Polygon functioning.</li>
    </ul>
  </ul>
  </div>
  <p>You are chosen to be a member of Polygon because we entrust you to develop amazing problems. If you are a hacker aiming to test system security,
  we suggest you to test it on the Online Judge system.</p>
  <p><strong>
    If keeping Polygon open is to become a security risk rather than a smart move, you will have no choice but to limit Polygon to internal use only.
  </strong></p>
  <form class="ui form {% if register_error %}error{% endif %}" method="POST">
    {% csrf_token %}
    <div class="field">
      <div class="ui checkbox">
        <input type="checkbox" tabindex="0" name="terms" class="hidden">
        <label>I agree terms of use.</label>
      </div>
      <div class="ui error message">
        <p>{{ register_error }}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <button class="ui button" type="submit">Submit</button>
  </form>

{% endblock %}

{% block script %}
  <script>
  $('.ui.form')
    .form({
      fields: {
        terms    : 'checked'
      }
    })
  ;
  </script>
{% endblock %}